ll,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe subtalar joint is located between the talus and calcaneus bones in the foot. It plays a crucial role in foot movements, particularly in adapting to uneven surfaces. The subtalar joint\u0027s primary function is to allow the foot to adapt to uneven surfaces through inversion and eversion, contributing to the overall movement of supination.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe correct movement associated with the subtalar joint is \u003Cstrong\u003Esupination\u003C/strong\u003E. Supination involves a combination of inversion, adduction, and plantarflexion of the foot, which is facilitated by the subtalar joint.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDorsiflexion\u003C/strong\u003E - This movement occurs at the ankle joint, not the subtalar joint\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPlantarflexion\u003C/strong\u003E - Like dorsiflexion, this occurs at the ankle joint\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERotation\u003C/strong\u003E - The subtalar joint does not primarily facilitate rotational movements\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EA-P glide\u003C/strong\u003E - Anterior-posterior glide is not a primary movement of the subtalar joint\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The subtalar joint is responsible for inversion and eversion movements of the foot.","Supination is a combination of inversion, adduction, and plantarflexion of the foot.","The subtalar joint does not facilitate dorsiflexion or plantarflexion, which occur at the ankle joint."],"references":["Patton, K. T., \u0026 Thibodeau, G. A. (2018). Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book: Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Smith, R., \u0026 Wordsworth, P. (2016). Oxford textbook of clinical and biochemical disorders of the skeleton. Oxford University Press","Sud, A., \u0026 Ranjan, R. (2021). Textbook of Orthopaedics, 2e-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Dandy, D. J., \u0026 Edwards, D. J. (2009). Essential Orthopaedics and Trauma E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","MacGregor R, Byerly DW. Anatomy, Bony Pelvis and Lower Limb: Foot Bones. 2023 May 23. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32491379"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59877"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18368"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59877","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/59877"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-25T05:01:09+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-24T09:33:12+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11086"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74386"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{